  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, several smartphones are known to be great options under \u20b912,000 in India. The best choice can depend on your specific preferences for features such as camera quality, battery life, performance, and software experience. Here are a few popular models that are generally recommended within this budget:\n\n1. **Realme Narzo 50A**:\n   -Good performance with MediaTek Helio G85 processor.\n   -Large battery (5000mAh) for long usage.\n   -Decent triple-camera setup.\n\n2. **Xiaomi Redmi Note 11**:\n   -Strong performance with Snapdragon 680.\n   -Vibrant AMOLED display.\n   -Good camera performance and battery life.\n\n3. **Samsung Galaxy M32**:\n   -Super AMOLED display with high refresh rate.\n   -Decent battery life (6000mAh).\n   -Good camera capabilities.\n\n4. **Poco M4 Pro**:\n   -Strong performance with MediaTek Dimensity 810.\n   -Fast charging capabilities.\n   -Good display quality.\n\n5. **iQOO Z6 Lite 5G**:\n   -5G support and good performance.\n   -Solid battery life.\n   -Attractive design.\n\n6. **Motorola Moto G31**:\n   -Stock Android experience.\n   -Good camera quality.\n   -Decent battery life.\n\nPrices and availability can vary, and it is always a good idea to check for the latest reviews and comparisons. Make sure to consider your priorities in terms of features when making a purchase.",
